feat(seed): production boot does TOP100 5y backfill + 2y signal replay

Render's Postgres was empty after the migration to the new universe
because backend/scripts/seed_data.py still pointed at the old 13-symbol
full_data_pipeline. Result: live /api/v1/brief showed regime=unknown,
sectors=0, signals=0 even though the local DB had 3,291 evaluated
signals + 114k OHLCV rows.

Changes
- backend/scripts/seed_data.py
  Stage A (always): runs scripts/top100_backfill.run(years=SEED_YEARS)
  when DailyPrice rows < SEED_MIN_ROWS. Covers the full curated
  universe of ~90 symbols.
  Stage B (opt-in via SEED_REPLAY=true): replays SEED_REPLAY_YEARS years
  through the production trade-plan engine to seed edge_signals, then
  walk-forward evaluates them so live performance / brief / scanner
  show real numbers from day one.
  Both stages are fault-tolerant — failure never blocks the web service
  from starting.

- render.yaml
  Defaults set for production:
    SEED_YEARS=5         (≈1240 bars/symbol)
    SEED_MIN_ROWS=1000   (cover threshold for full backfill)
    SEED_REPLAY=true     (run the 2y replay on first boot)
    SEED_REPLAY_YEARS=2

Local stats reproduce these defaults: 92 symbols at ≥1000 bars,
3,291 walk-forward evaluations, overall PF=1.33, expectancy=+0.08R.

Tests: 132/132 green.

